Author: Alice Gabrielli
Subject: shift summary DAY
Text:
Shifters:
Alice, Rasmus, Chistian


After replacing the DUT many runs with 8b10b error --> run goes to error and stop acquisition

Runs with errors are not saved?? for sure not in the elog

Checked cables but ok.

Tried to change 

self.daq.rx_channels['rx0']['DATA_DELAY'] = 24

with different values the error is more frequent.

Instead with 24 we have few runs with 1M events.

Decided to reduce the number of events to about 500k, still ok for in-pixel efficiency.

Author: Alice Gabrielli
Subject: shift summary
Text:
****  Shifters ****
* Roua Boudagga, Guglielmo Benfratello, Yannik Buch

Continued working on the HVC of the W8R4

Run 1980 : HV 35, 40C, Standard settings (ICASN=5)
Run 1981 : Bad, memory full

While waiting did different tunings for the W8R4 at high threshold

Run 1982 : HV 35, 45C, ICASN 30
Run 1983 : HV 35, 45C, ICASN 10
Run 1984 : HV 35, 45C, ICASN 80
Run 1985 : HV 35, 45C, ICASN 9, IBIAS 65 --> THR = 25
Run 1986 : HV 35, 45C, ICASN 10, IBIAS 65, ITHR 50 --> THR = 30
Run 1987 : HV 35, 45C, ICASN 10, IBIAS 65, ITHR 70 --> THR = 35
Runs 1988-1989 : Bad, TJMP2 needed powercycling
Run 1990 : HV 35, 40C, ICASN 80
Run 1991 : HV 4, 30C, standard settings (ICASN 30)
Run 1992 : Bad, HV 3, 30C, no hits in DUT AFTER analysis
Run 1993 : HV 2, 30C, standard settings
Run 1994 : HVC but psub 6V, 30C, standard settings
Run 1995 : HV 3, 30C, standard settings, retook run 1992
Run 1996 : Bad, after terminating the EUDAQ run control to be sure that the error of run 1992 couldn't eventually propagate further, forgot to enable Telepix
Run 1997 : HV 35, 25C, standard settings
Run 1998 : HV 35, 20C, standard settings
Run 1999 : HV 35, 15C, standard settings
Run 2000 : HV 35, 10C, standard settings

Author: Alice Gabrielli
Subject: Shift summary
Text:
Shifters:
Christian Bespin, Max Babeluk, Rasmus Partzsch, Guglielmo Benfratello, Alice Gabrielli

Repleaced AIDA-mode adapter to connect TLU to bdaq board
After that many issues and not fully possible to check if everything is working fine

Debug runs: 1873--> not possible to analyse (could be that the DUT was flashing???)

Crosschecked timestamp in "BAD" runs and "GOOD" runs with AIDA mode.  In "BAD" runs the timestamp from TJMonopix was reset, while now is not. So probably now the AIDAmode is working (?)

Moved from debug runs to beam runs to not loose beam time... while waiting for working analysis

W2R5: 3 runs at different temperature (run 1876-1877-1877)

Analysis apparently started working again.
What we would like to check?? One week ago we had synchronisation issues after ~60 sec with AIDA mode. Do we still have it?

Changed DUT from W2R5 to W8R6.

1 run with DCC, psub=20V, std settings: 1880
1 looong run HVC (during dinner), HV=40V, std settings: 1881 --> after stopping the eu_run was not responding anymore, force quit


During dinner long alignment but after not possible to analyse the data (RAM out of memory)


Another run HVC, HV=40V, std settings, forgot telepix

Another run HVC, HV=40V, std settings

Meanwhile: YES-YES from the huts: AIDA mode works, also for the analysis!

Author: Yannik Buch
Subject: mask file for hvc w2r5
Text:
Yuka

New mask txt files were created for each of the runs: 1790 - 1802. 
Looking into those mask txt files, it was found that they were identical.
Therefore, analysis for those runs were conducted again with /geo/updated_geo/geo_id6_1790.geo which contains the mask file for run 1790, which is also identical to the other mask files created for those runs.

Analysis of run 1806 and 1807 used geo_id6_1806_07.geo which is the geometry file for run 1803 but with mask file of run 1806 as the mask file for 1806 and 1807 were identical.


Re-aligned at run 1808 with mask file of run 1808. 

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

For runs analysed at the beginning of the test beam (1679) (note: may not be W2R5), seems like mask file was not applied. geo_id5_eudet.geo is used to re-analyse. much better analysis.

Author: Yannik Buch
Subject: Mimosa troubleshooting steps
Text:
This is for reference from previous testbeams.
The error seen during the past few days were of different nature as the raw files for the telescope were written but were almost empty or some trigger numbers 
randomly jumped in the telescope files. These are apparently fixed by not using "reset" button in eudaq and instead terminating and starting again.
But if you observe something to the effect of the following this might be helpful.
If telescope is init'ing and configuring as normal but it produces no raw files try these steps:

In "new_MIMOSA_DAQ-USE_THIS.exe" (or similar) on NI_crate PC (you may use remmina to log onto that pc) 
Press the stop symbol on top of the window and then the arrow next to it. If this goes though without error this might be good enough already. Try to take data.
If it errors with "Error Config Socket" or there are still no raw files written try to reprogram the mimosas.
open MIMOSA JTAG MASTER configuration via MI26.exe-Shortcut
Main-> Device Update
Press 
1. Reset
2. All
3. Read
4. Start
Then press stop button and arrow as before and restart eudaq and try to take data again.
The picture below has the original manual from 2022 Testbeam.

Text:
****  Shifters ****
* Guglielmo Benfratello, Yuka Okada, Yannik Buch, Alice Gabrielli, (Maximilian Babeluk, Bernhard Pilsl)

we wanted to resolve the problems affecting the night shift's runs.
changed TLU, removed ground cable.

still problems with Mimosa acquisition.
Found a 'stable' procedure (after run 1794), in which we never use 'Reset' but only reconfigure before restarting the run.
Threshold scans need to be done only at the end of the measurements with a set temperature AFTER terminating the eudaq run control.

We repeat the measurements failed during the night and continue with HVC

Comment settings:
EUDET mode, T_NTC = 30C, standard settings

HVC frontend

run 1774 used to check sync with the new TLU

run 1775: HV = 25V, low efficiency, not sure about efficiency (88%)/alignment, reran with 1790

run 1776-1778: HV = 25V, debug runs

Switch to DCC
Tried to see the stability of the modified setup with the DCC frontend

psub = 20V

runs 1779-1783: debug runs for DCC, also reducing number of rows to 430, since they are not used in the tracking

run 1784: 

run 1785: elog test

run 1786: DCC run with standard columns enabled and rows 0-430 (bad: no tracks)

back to HVC
HV = 25 V

runs 1787 - 1789: bad, readout stuck or wrong configuration

run 1790: good, effi 99.3 %

run 1791: HV = 20V, bad (no tracks)

run 1792: HV = 15V, bad (error in MIMOSA)

run 1794: HV = 15V, good, effi 98.9 %

runs 1795-1800: HV=20V, debug to test

Author: Xu Danwei
Subject: shift summary
Text:
****  Shifters ****
* Wang shijie, Giuliana Rizzo, Xu DANWEI

change chip to W2R5, Same telescope position
changed config ID to 6

we want to first do alignment with DCC and then do bias scan with HVC
but we observed there is 'flashing' appeared
tried to reduce the number of cols and increase the THR but still flashing. 

we enetered and grounded the BDAQ board. 
After this we still cannot run the noise scan, BUT we could use the matrcix with the col 360-448 with the producer and see noise hits. 
So we decided to take beam data even if noise scan is not possible. 
No flashing seen after grounding the BDAQ board

Comment settings:
EUDET mode, T_NTC = 30C psub = 20V, standard settings

Text:
Shifters: G. Rizzo, C. Irmler, B. Pilsl

Continue HVC at high T_NTC=40C with HV=40V and lowering THR (default was THR=18) 
Possibly try with BCID OFF or HV=45V

Then continue with DCC with low temperature


We see that HVC data needs to be re-aligned since the residuals are OFF by 40 um from first run 1707 on HVC
Bernard is re-aligning one of the HVC run now (1730) then he will apply this alignment to other runs of HVC,  from 1707 to the last one to seee the effect 

Run 1732 with HVC HV=40V T_NTC=40C ICASN=70 THR=14.8 Effi 98.8% (after re-alignment) 

Efficiency is still at the limit 

try to increase ICASN more to lower THR to 13 or 12? if not possible we will do it with the BCID OFF 

Several noise scan (only 10 s)  with ICASN=50,70, 80, 90, 100 at 100 chip was stuck , BEAM was on by mistake. but from TOT it was from noise. 

Redo it with ICASN=90 no beams

if I try scan threshold on 2 cols instead the readout is blocked and no hits??? 

retry with ICASN=90 10s noise scan ok,

retry same scan thresho

Author: Alice Gabrielli
Subject: shift summary
Text:
Shifters:  Giuliana, Yuka 

After run 1661 at T_NTC 25C,  with new position of the DUT, I moved to T_NTC to 30C T_Cu = 30.5C to start the program measurement 
Analysis says in this run there is no correlation it seems that 

Temperature reached T_NTC=30C  and currents are OK 
Set Beam OFF to run the noise scans and thr scans 
taken files h5 from lab test 
scan noise done OK 
20250402_203509_noise_occupancy_scan_interpreted

scan threshold with BCID ON and reset inj 0-140 DAC 
20250402_204214_threshold_scan_interpreted
THR = 27.4+/- 0.7 DAC 
Noise = 3.42 DAC 

scan threshold with BCID ON w/o reset inj 0-140 DAC 
/home/bellevtx01/vtx/tj-monopix-daq-tb25/tjmonopix2/scans/output_data/module_0/chip_0/20250402_205211_threshold_scan_interpreted.h5
THR = 34.0 +/- 1.1 DAC 
Noise = 4.0 DAC 

prepare for the run config file prepared  with the scan thr with BCID ON 
Start high stat run at T_NTC=30C bias -20V 
~ 15 min run each 1.3 Mevts each 

run 1662 started at 21:08 stopped at 21:25 with ~ 1.7Mevts (don't know if it was analysed) 

while starting the new run by mistake I didn't configure so there were errors so try reset then terminate and restart all


run 1664 started at 21:55 stopped at 22:11 with ~ 1.5Mevts BUT e-log entry was not created. The sync was lost after 15 sec  

We saw from the analysis 2 different problems:  

1.  The runs loose the sync after a few sec/min? AIDA mode is not working with this unstable sync!

2. the Cupper is probabl
